{
  "stem": "3928.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I seen this happen, but I cannot be overly, you know, suspicious to go there and look everything, or question anything like it, you know, because I didn't want to blow my cover, so to speak-- you know, or put not just me, but the whole organization of danger.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because as far as I know, I was the only inside man they had.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was the only one who can give them the information, as far as I know.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And-- and the only person who was my contact man was Mr.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Schweikert.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "If he had more, I don't know about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- and the Swedish diplomat, I didn't know until the day he was taken with these Russian guards.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was Raoul Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I know he was a Swedish diplomat because-- you know, the less I learned by being taught by very good-- by some people who were in intelligence and the resistance-- you don't ask questions, and you don't remember names.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because if you get captured, everybody has a certain point of resistance when you just break.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "If you don't know, you can say nothing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But if you know something, you know, to come to a breaking point when you want to spill everything hoping to save you-- and if you don't know, you don't have to worry about anything because you can-- they kill you anyhow.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was their-- their favorite thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The favorite thing was their-- their-- for the SS and the-- and-- and the Nazis, when they arrested maybe three people, and they took them up, for instance, in the SS headquarters, and demand one man to let three men sit together and ask them questions.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And if one man aggravated them, wouldn't talk, they took him to another room, and shot off the pistol.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
